’s central claims about atonement, Jesus’ death and resurrection, and divine recompense emerge from this conceptual matrix. By tracing the narrative development of the economic motif, the author explains how Jesus saves his people from their sins and comes to be enthroned as Son of Man, sheds new light on numerous exegetical puzzles, and clarifies the relationship of ethical rigorism and divine generosity.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 4aMatthäusevangelium. 4aRechtschaffenheit. 4aSühne. 4aSünde. 4aWirtschaftssprache. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Studies / New Testament.2bisacsh  aGospel of Matthew.  aatonement.  adebt of sin.  alanguage of economy.  aransom.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110638165oZDB-23-GTR08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2013z9783110317350oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE THEOLOGY, JUDAISM, RELIGION  2013z978311031734308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET THEOLOGIE, RELIGIONSWISS., JUDAISTIK  2013z9783110317336oZDB-23-DGF08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertReligious Studies De Gruyterz97831107168250 cprintz978311030384140uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311030407740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110304077423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110304077/original  a978-3-11-023854-9  DGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c2000d2014  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA 